{"title":"Meet the New Soft & Grippy Race Face Chester MTB Grip","link":"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-chester-mtb-grip/","date":1701441839000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip Hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-Hero-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Race Face, a <a href=\"https://www.raceface.com/\">long-time player</a> in the quality bicycle component game, just introduced its softest, tackiest, and <a href=\"https://www.raceface.com/products/chester-grip?variant=40610738602066\">most advanced MTB grip</a> ever. Called the Chester mountain bike grip, Race Face borrows the name from their also-grippy Chester pedals. Race Face says that this grip was developed through feedback from riders and racers to ensure this grip ticked all of the boxes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"673\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292-800x673.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip thick ends\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292-800x673.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292-297x250.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292-120x101.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292-768x646.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-thick-ends-e1701378164292.jpeg 851w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Race Face)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Race Face’s Chester line of products is about the nitty gritty. No fluff just purpose-built products centered on functionality and durability. It’s less about having the lightest or fanciest build and more about riding “when and how you want to”. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, that being said, let’s check out what the Chester Grip is all about. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Race Face Chester Grip</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Increased Thickness</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Chester Grip has a perforated core design that allows more 20A Durometer rubber to sit between your hands and the bar. With a concentrated thickness under the palm, the rider increases ride comfort and reduces fatigue. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip wedged thumb spot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot-768x1151.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-wedged-thumb-spot.jpeg 854w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip ribbed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed-768x1151.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-ribbed.jpeg 854w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The angled mushroom ribs help to wick away moisture for those of you who like to ride gloveless. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Better Gription…</strong>wait, is that a word?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>“Grip and Find Out” is Race Face’s slogan for the Chester Grip release. Well, grips wouldn’t be doing their job without keeping your hands in place, and this grip seems to have some features to help in that area. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs-800x552.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip shallow ribs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs-800x552.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs-297x205.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs-120x83.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs-768x530.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-shallow-ribs.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs-800x552.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip no ribs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs-800x552.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs-297x205.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs-120x83.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs-768x530.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-no-ribs.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Raised ridges and a recessed finger pad give the rider precise grip feedback that can be lost on some other MTB grips. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Express Yourself</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are a whopping seven anodized clamp colors that are available. So you’ll be able to get all matchy-matchy to your heart’s content. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"862\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690-800x862.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690-800x862.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690-278x300.jpeg 278w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690-111x120.jpeg 111w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690-768x828.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-colors-e1701378382690.jpeg 851w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s go over the colors:  Black, Turquoise, Purple, Kashmoney, Orange, Silver, Blue, Red, Forest Green, and (my favorite) Gum colored grip with a black clamp. Have fun! </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"804\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961-800x804.jpeg\" alt=\"Race Face Chester MT Grip full rib upright\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961-800x804.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961-297x298.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961-768x772.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Race-Face-Chester-MT-Grip-full-rib-upright-e1701378464961.jpeg 851w\" /></a><figcaption>My fave!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Chester Specs and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $27</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Diameter: 31mm and 34mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Material: 20A Durometer Rubber</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Length: 136mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 112g (31mm pair), 135g (34mm pair)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.raceface.com/\">RaceFace.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/race-face-chester-mtb-grip/\">Meet the New Soft &amp; Grippy Race Face Chester MTB Grip</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8e74c22730f829bc3383113419512816c1a6b9a2c90dde33bfee62e835325ece","category":"Cycling"}